(b) The Christ-life does not make any rite or doctrine cz test of spiritual life

In both cases when Jesus in his human ministry conformed to our need of outwardness he ran counter to all formerly established tests of piety. In the one case he moved in harmony with the emotional crowd at a great revival meeting3 in the other he went alone to make atonement between God and man, by an act which revolted every pious conception.
